07:40.593 --> 07:42.720
I am a great man.

07:42.795 --> 07:45.161
And great men do great things.

07:46.666 --> 07:49.396
I want to open a flagship store
right here in Philadelphia.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.733
I want it to be the
biggest store we ever built,

07:51.804 --> 07:55.001
I want it to be made
of 100% recyclable materials,

07:55.074 --> 07:59.477
and I want it to be so beautiful
that people want to get married in it.

08:03.249 --> 08:05.149
Kate, join me up here.

08:07.119 --> 08:09.952
I'm wearing a dress, Barry.

08:10.022 --> 08:11.785
Won't you?

08:11.858 --> 08:12.950
Sure.

08:18.231 --> 08:19.391
Okay.

08:25.104 --> 08:29.336
Kate, I want you to spearhead
this as our new vice president.

08:30.710 --> 08:34.510
This is me transferring
my success to you.

08:40.785 --> 08:42.378
Thank you, Barry.

08:42.989 --> 08:44.251
Hold on.

08:51.831 --> 08:52.820
Thanks.

08:55.268 --> 08:56.792
Congratulations.
- Yeah.

08:58.137 --> 08:59.798
Thank you.
- Congratulations, Kate.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.542
Hello.
I'm Chaffee Bicknell.

09:46.085 --> 09:47.814
There's just one of you.

09:47.887 --> 09:51.448
I thought Chaffee and Bicknell
were two different people.

09:56.128 --> 09:57.390
Come in.
- Certainly.

10:01.734 --> 10:05.226
I started this business
because I saw a growth market.

10:05.304 --> 10:07.295
We don't do
our own taxes anymore.

10:07.373 --> 10:09.102
We don't program
our computers.

10:09.175 --> 10:10.506
We outsource.

10:10.576 --> 10:13.545
And what is surrogacy
if not outsourcing?

10:13.613 --> 10:15.581
