bet you love it and you're good at it.

10:53.819 --> 10:56.287
Let me ask you a question.

10:56.355 --> 10:58.118
Do you plan on hiring a nanny?

10:58.190 --> 11:00.454
Of course.
I have to go back to work.

11:00.526 --> 11:02.153
How is this any different?

11:02.228 --> 11:06.562
A nanny is someone you trust to take
care of your baby after it's born.

11:06.632 --> 11:11.763
A surrogate mother is someone you trust
to take care of your baby before it's born.

11:11.837 --> 11:14.169
Either way it's your baby.

11:15.641 --> 11:17.404
And here's my baby.

11:18.377 --> 11:21.813
Hello, my sweetheart.
Hello, little one.

11:21.881 --> 11:26.045
Oh, yes.
What a good girl. Yes.

11:27.353 --> 11:29.048
Everyone deserves this.

11:29.121 --> 11:32.454
That's why I wanna remove
the stigma from surrogacy.

11:32.558 --> 11:35.584
There's no wrong way
to make a family.

11:35.695 --> 11:37.424
And you're proof of that.

11:37.496 --> 11:39.088
How do you mean?

11:39.165 --> 11:42.100
Just that you have this
beautiful baby using surrogacy.

11:42.168 --> 11:43.192
Oh, no.

11:43.269 --> 11:46.898
My husband and I conceived
Sabrina the old-fashioned way.

11:46.972 --> 11:48.599
But you're so...
- Old?

11:49.709 --> 11:52.473
You wouldn't think so
if you saw my uterus.

11:52.545 --> 11:55.981
But you know what really made
this little angel possible?

11:56.048 --> 11:57.675
A time machine?

11:57.750 --> 11:59.445
A positive attitude.

11:59.518 --> 12:01.486
You may not have
my fertile body,

12:01.554 --> 12:04.546
but with my help
you can still be a mother.

