in the next cool neighborhood.

20:32.965 --> 20:34.523
It can be open lots.

20:34.600 --> 20:36.795
<i>It can be buildings that
we buy and tear down,</i>

20:36.868 --> 20:38.130
<i>although
no historic buildings.</i>

20:38.203 --> 20:40.671
We want to be perceived
as enhancing the neighborhood,

20:40.739 --> 20:42.502
not destroying
its character.

20:42.574 --> 20:48.513
Also, Barry would like to use
mostly found and recycled materials.

20:48.580 --> 20:50.639
<i>So that's gonna affect us,
zoning-wise.</i>

20:51.316 --> 20:53.580
I don't care what we spend,
but we have to get it right.

21:13.372 --> 21:15.772
Shannon! Dante! Anybody?

21:20.712 --> 21:24.239
Sorry about that. Welcome to
Super Fruity. What can I get you?

21:24.316 --> 21:27.342
Does the Orange You
Glad I Didn't Say Banana?

21:27.419 --> 21:29.979
in fact contain banana?

21:30.055 --> 21:32.023
Yeah. Yeah,
but it's a good question.

21:32.090 --> 21:35.321
I think the name's a little more
clever than it is informative.

21:35.394 --> 21:37.089
Well, I will try it.

21:37.195 --> 21:38.184
Okay.

21:39.531 --> 21:41.658
Hey, I'm looking
for a new apartment.

21:41.733 --> 21:43.428
What is your read
on this neighborhood?

21:43.502 --> 21:47.836
The neighborhood's good.
It's good. It's changing a lot.

21:47.906 --> 21:50.033
A lot of condos going up.

21:50.108 --> 21:52.372
The real estate people
are trying to give it one of those

21:53.712 --> 21:55.873
clever names,
they call it WeBeSoCa,

21:55.947 --> 21:59.849
which is Webster, south
of Catherine, I guess.

22:00.686 --> 22:02.449
How's business?

22:05.123 --> 22:06.681
It's a little slow.

22:06.758 --> 22:11.559
But kind of tough, you know,
going up against the man.

22:11.630 --> 22:12.688
The cops?

22:12.764 --> 22:13.788
Jamba Juice.

22:13.865 --> 22:15.093
Jamba Juice is the man?

22:15.167 --> 22:16.191
Yeah.

22:16.268 --> 22:17.428
Corporate juice pimps.

22:17.502 --> 22:19.697
Thought you should know, and you'll
feel free to tell your friends.

22:19.771 --> 22:21.705
Okay. I will tell them.

22:24.476 --> 22:27.240
Okay, now.
You have a super fruity day.

22:32.217 --> 22:33.309
I want you to start
finding out

22:33.385 --> 22:38.448
what's available between the 1500 block
and 1800 block of West Catherine Street.

22:39.925 --> 22:42.189
Ron, I gotta call you back.

22:42.260 --> 22:43.784
Angie?
- Hi, it's Angie.

22:43.862 --> 22:46.092
I know. I know.
So, any news?

22:46.164 --> 22:49.031
Well, I peed on one of those
stick thingies, and it said yes.

22:50.535 --> 22:52.162
Angie, that is just
the greatest news!

22:52.237 --> 22:53.761
That's just
unbelievably great.

22:53.839 --> 22:54.828
Yeah, yeah.

22:55.507 --> 22:56.735
Thank you so much, Angie.

22:56.808 --> 23:00.266
If you need anything, anything
at all, you let me know, okay?

23:00.345 --> 23:01.573
Yeah, okay. I will.

23:03.348 --> 23:04.906
I'm having a baby!

23:33.678 --> 23:34.667
Hello.

23:34.746 --> 23:36.737
What if the baby's
a hermaphrodite?

23:36.815 --> 23:37.804
<i>What?</i>

23:37.883 --> 23:39.475
A chick with a dick.

23:39.551 --> 23:41.883
I heard it happens
to about 2% of babies.

23:41.953 --> 23:43.250
Well, that's crazy.

23:43.321 --> 23:45.789
That would mean that 10 people from
our high school were hermaphrodites.

23:45.857 --> 23:46.949
Mommy. Mommy.
Mommy. Mommy.

23:47.025 --> 23:48.549
No, that sounds
about right, actually.

23:48.627 --> 23:51.323
You can't solve problems
by worrying about them.

23:51.396 --> 23:53.728
Is that Alex? What does
she want for her birthday?

23:53.799 --> 23:57.200
Karaoke Revolution
or a cell phone.

23:57.269 --> 23:58.600
She's four.

23:59.638 --> 24:02.732
Do you think it's too much if I
ask Angie to call me every day?

24:02.808 --> 24:04.673
She just seems so chaotic.

24:04.743 --> 24:05.903
I don't know
if she's eating right.

24:05.977 --> 24:07.239
Is she getting
enough exercise?

24:07.312 --> 24:08.939
Is she moving around too much?

24:09.014 --> 24:10.242
You're only six weeks in.

24:10.315 --> 24:13.045
<i>You can't put her in a cage
and force-feed her.</i>

24:13.118 --> 24:14.278
I know. I know.

24:14.352 --> 24:15.649
Expecting a baby?

24:16.421 --> 24:18.184
Did I tell you? I found a
location for the new store.

24:18.256 --> 24:19.348
Yeah, I have to
pitch it tomorrow.

24:19.424 --> 24:22.985
It's gonna be a girl. That's
what's making your hair so dry.

24:23.094 --> 24:24.493
Cash or credit?

24:24.563 --> 24:25.587
Cash.

24:45.183 --> 24:46.343
Oscar?

24:49.588 --> 24:51.385
You got baby mama drama.

24:51.490 --> 24:54.050
Hey, I left Carl.

24:54.125 --> 24:57.561
I found out he was effing around
on me, so we got into a huge fight.

24:57.629 --> 24:59.290
Things got
really physical.

24:59.364 --> 25:00.456
Oh, my God.
Are you okay?

25:00.532 --> 25:02.261
Yeah. I didn't
hit him too hard.

25:02.334 --> 25:04.734
Hey, I brought you
a picture of the baby.

25:04.803 --> 25:07.169
You know,
an ultrasound picture.

25:07.239 --> 25:08.706
Oh, my gosh.

25:11.476 --> 25:13.068
Looks like a squirrel.

25:14.212 --> 25:16.339
A cute, cute squirrel.

25:16.414 --> 25:18.712
Anyway, it's kind of early, so
you can't really see anything,

25:18.783 --> 25:21.616
but they took a picture of it just
to make sure it's growing right.

25:21.686 --> 25:22.948
They said all the parts
are good.

25:23.021 --> 25:25.148
Why didn't you tell me?
I would've been there.

25:25.223 --> 25:27.657
I didn't want
to bother you.

25:36.935 --> 25:39.836
Don't worry. This couch is
more comfortable than it looks.

25:39.905 --> 25:44.205
I also put a stack of clean
towels for you in the bathroom.

25:44.276 --> 25:46.540
Do you need
a toothbrush?

25:46.645 --> 25:49.739
Because I have some extras
that I keep for houseguests.

25:57.055 --> 25:58.852
Good night, squirrel.

26:06.131 --> 26:09.362
What we have here is our Boo
Boo Buster No-Slam Door, okay?

26:09.434 --> 26:10.423
Watch how this works.

26:10.502 --> 26:13.630
You can just slam it.
It bounces right back.

26:13.705 --> 26:15.832
So you can put your fingers right
on in there, and it wouldn't...

26:15.907 --> 26:17.966
Not you, it'll only
work for baby fingers.

26:18.043 --> 26:19.305
Okay.
- Okay?

26:20.612 --> 26:23.080
Also included
in your premium package,

26:23.148 --> 26:25.616
we have
child protection everywhere.

26:26.885 --> 26:30.082
The doors, the door handles,
you have the cabinets,

26:31.189 --> 26:34.215
caps all over the outlets,
cabinets, everything.

26:34.292 --> 26:36.886
It's just baby-proof
all over the place.

26:36.962 --> 26:40.398
Shouldn't be a problem for
anybody over the age of seven.

26:46.037 --> 26:47.299
You sure have
done a great job

26:47.372 --> 26:49.169
getting an early jump
on your baby-proofing.

26:49.240 --> 26:50.434
Well, you guys
are the best in the city,

26:50.508 --> 26:51.998
and I didn't want to risk
being on a waiting list.

26:52.077 --> 26:56.104
True. But you can't be no more
than three, four months pregnant.

27:07.192 --> 27:09.422
There's something
wrong with your toilet.

27:09.894 --> 27:11.759
I'm sorry I broke
one of your rules.

27:11.830 --> 27:14.355
You peed in the sink. Isn't
that against everyone's rules?

27:14.432 --> 27:16.798
Only a crazy person
locks their toilet.

27:16.868 --> 27:18.995
It's for the baby.
It's safe.

27:19.070 --> 27:20.401
Please don't touch
anything else.

27:32.350 --> 27:34.250
I'm here. I'm here. I'm sorry.

27:34.319 --> 27:35.877
45 minutes late.
This isn't like you.

27:35.954 --> 27:38.684
I'm sorry, Barry. I'm just
a little out of whack today.

27:38.757 --> 27:41.225
Want me to get Dr. Gary down here?
Give you a shot of bee pollen?

27:41.292 --> 27:43.351
No, thank you. I'm
good. Let's do this.

27:43.428 --> 27:45.259
Thank you
for waiting, everyone.

27:45.363 --> 27:48.230
This may look like a
dilapidated warehouse...

27:48.967 --> 27:51.595
<i>Lady Luck gets on my side</i>

27:51.670 --> 27:54.264
<i>We're gonna rock
this town alive</i>

27:54.973 --> 27:56.099
<i>I'll let her
rough me up</i>

27:56.207 --> 27:57.196
Thanks, Oscar.

27:57.275 --> 27:58.264
<i>She knocks me out</i>

27:58.343 --> 28:01.835
<i>She walks like she talks
like she talks like she walks</i>

28:01.913 --> 28:03.141
<i>She bangs, she bangs</i>

28:03.214 --> 28:05.341
<i>Hey.
- What are you doing?</i>

28:05.417 --> 28:06.509
What is this mess?

28:06.584 --> 28:07.642
<i>Oh, baby, she moves, she moves</i>

28:07.719 --> 28:09.914
This game is awesome.
Where did you get this?

28:09.988 --> 28:12.047
That's supposed to be
my niece's birthday present.

28:12.123 --> 28:13.147
Sorry.

28:13.224 --> 28:14.782
Angie, what kind of food is
this for a pregnant woman?

28:14.859 --> 28:18.488
Dr. Pepper, Pringles, Tastykakes?

28:20.031 --> 28:21.589
Red Bull?

28:21.666 --> 28:24.134
Angie, Red Bull?

28:24.202 --> 28:27.638
You have to remember that you are
carrying something very precious.

28:27.706 --> 28:29.230
Like a little puppy.
- Yeah.

28:29.340 --> 28:30.500
Yeah. Or a baby.

28:30.575 --> 28:35.205
What you eat, the baby eats. What
you listen to, the baby listens to.

28:35.280 --> 28:37.339
If you listen to DMX,
the baby comes out going...

28:40.919 --> 28:42.181
Are those cigarettes?

28:42.253 --> 28:43.413
What? No. Where?

28:43.488 --> 28:46.116
Do you know how stupid
it is to smoke at all,

28:46.191 --> 28:47.624
let alone when
you are pregnant?

28:47.692 --> 28:49.284
I'm not smoking.
I swear, I'm not...

28:53.331 --> 28:55.424
Why would you
answer my phone?

28:55.500 --> 28:57.092
<i>Hello.
- Kate, we're moving forward.</i>

28:57.168 --> 28:59.693
I think that that
is a great decision, Barry.

28:59.771 --> 29:03.969
Yes, let's get those facts and
figures, Barry, into the idea machine.

29:04.042 --> 29:05.100
<i>We should close
in a couple of weeks.</i>

29:05.176 --> 29:07.144
<i>I want you to put together
a press conference.</i>

29:07.245 --> 29:09.975
How about we start with a
little community outreach

29:10.048 --> 29:11.811
and get the people in the
neighborhood on our side,

29:11.883 --> 29:13.783
and then let the press
find us?

29:13.852 --> 29:17.117
That's why I'm a genius
for hiring people like you.

29:19.524 --> 29:21.515
All right, you.

29:21.593 --> 29:23.925
My job gives me access
to the most nutritious,

29:23.995 --> 29:25.189
chemical-free food
in the world.

29:25.263 --> 29:28.562
I don't want my kid born addicted
to high-fructose corn syrup.

29:28.633 --> 29:33.434
There is a thing called being too
healthy. That's what killed Bruce Lee.

29:33.538 --> 29:36.564
<i>Really? Where did you read
that? The Weekly World Dum-Dum?</i>

29:36.641 --> 29:41.271
All right. This is your folic acid
and this is your pre-natal vitamin.

29:41.346 --> 29:42.643
You're serious about this?

29:42.714 --> 29:45.444
I don't want my baby
to have a pinhead.

29:46.017 --> 29:47.348
I can't do it.

29:47.418 --> 29:49.818
I got it. It's going...

29:49.888 --> 29:51.651
I can't swallow it.

29:55.627 --> 29:56.719
What is this?

29:56.795 --> 29:57.819
Water.

29:57.896 --> 29:59.659
It's horrible!

30:02.300 --> 30:04.165
I need a...
- No, I can't put it in your butt.

30:04.235 --> 30:06.533
Angie, cats can do this.
Come on.

30:06.604 --> 30:08.401
It's in there.
- Just try.

30:08.473 --> 30:09.770
Just relax.

30:09.841 --> 30:12.537
Close your eyes,
open your mouth,

30:13.578 --> 30:15.978
and do it! Swallow it.

30:16.080 --> 30:18.173
Take it. There you go! You did it.

30:20.752 --> 30:22.686
<i>Hey, I'm just
like a lot of you.</i>

30:22.754 --> 30:27.487
<i>I grew up at 52nd and Walnut.
I attended West Philly High.</i>

30:27.559 --> 30:31.222
<i>I smoked a joint with Hall & Oates
during the bicentennial, all of that.</i>

30:31.296 --> 30:33.127
<i>But unlike
a lot of you,</i>

30:33.198 --> 30:35.792
<i>I have since
traveled the world.</i>

30:35.867 --> 30:39.394
<i>I've had papaya on the
beach at Virgin Gorda.</i>

30:39.470 --> 30:43.463
<i>I've toasted pine nuts at the
mouth of an active volcano.</i>

30:43.575 --> 30:47.602
<i>I sat down with Native Americans
and had some amazing salmon.</i>

30:48.847 --> 30:51.338
<i>And I'm here to share
my experiences with you.</i>

30:51.416 --> 30:53.941
<i>You know, I was talking to Jimmy
Buffett this morning about trans fats...</i>

30:54.018 --> 30:55.883
Barry, the time.

30:56.988 --> 30:58.615
<i>Well, I'm sorry
I can't stay longer,</i>

30:58.690 --> 31:00.885
<i>but I have to swing by
my son's graduation.</i>

31:00.959 --> 31:02.187
<i>So I will turn you over</i>

31:02.260 --> 31:05.855
<i>to our vice president of
development, Ms. Kate Holbrook.</i>

31:10.168 --> 31:11.157
<i>Good morning and thank you...</i>

31:11.236 --> 31:12.464
Will there be pedestrian
access during construction?

31:12.537 --> 31:14.368
How can you charge
$4 for one mango?

31:14.439 --> 31:15.838
What's your
carbon footprint?

31:15.907 --> 31:18.808
<i>Okay, how about we line up down
front here at the microphone?</i>

31:18.877 --> 31:20.606
<i>And I can take
your questions...</i>

31:20.712 --> 31:23.613
<i>And I can take your
questions one at a time.</i>

31:24.782 --> 31:25.874
<i>Hi.</i>

31:26.684 --> 31:30.848
<i>Rob Ackerman, WeBeSoCa Small
Business Owners' Association,</i>

31:30.922 --> 31:34.358
<i>and I also own
Super Fruity Smoothies.</i>

31:34.425 --> 31:36.120
<i>It's like Jamba Juice.</i>

31:36.194 --> 31:39.254
<i>No, it's not. It's not
like Jamba Juice at all.</i>

31:40.732 --> 31:42.097
<i>I think you've been
to my store.</i>

31:42.166 --> 31:43.929
<i>Yes, I have. I remember.</i>

31:44.002 --> 31:46.562
<i>Did you ever find that
apartment you were looking for?</i>

31:47.705 --> 31:49.195
<i>Not yet. No.</i>

31:49.274 --> 31:51.868
<i>Here's my question. Exactly
what portion of your profits</i>

31:51.943 --> 31:53.103
<i>are gonna go
towards rebuilding</i>

31:53.177 --> 31:55.975
<i>and the revitalization
of our community?</i>

31:56.047 --> 31:57.275
Yes!

31:59.751 --> 32:02.015
<i>Thank you for that question.</i>

32:06.824 --> 32:09.554
Those are free, by the way.
You don't have to sneak them.

32:09.627 --> 32:12.460
All of this stuff
is our gift to you.

32:12.530 --> 32:13.758
Hey, Kate.

32:13.831 --> 32:15.458
Hi.

32:15.533 --> 32:16.693
What a spread.

32:16.768 --> 32:17.792
Thanks.

32:17.869 --> 32:19.427
So, I had one last
question for you.

32:19.504 --> 32:20.732
Okay.

32:20.805 --> 32:23.501
You never told me how
you liked the smoothie.

32:23.574 --> 32:26.509
Well, a little too much
banana for me.

32:26.577 --> 32:27.874
Wow.

32:28.846 --> 32:29.835
You know,
Mr. Ackerman...

32:29.914 --> 32:30.972
No, no, no.

32:31.049 --> 32:33.279
Mr. Ackerman's my dog.
You gotta call me Rob.

32:33.351 --> 32:36.013
Okay, Rob. I really
don't want any tension

32:36.087 --> 32:37.816
with the Small Business
Owners' Association.

32:37.889 --> 32:40.084
So I would be happy to sit
down with you some time and...

32:40.158 --> 32:41.523
You asking me
out on a date?

32:41.592 --> 32:42.616
No.

32:42.694 --> 32:45.094
You sure? 'Cause you
lied to me once already.

32:45.163 --> 32:47.996
Yes, I'm sure.

32:48.066 --> 32:49.897
See you around.

32:50.835 --> 32:54.931
And then he asked me if I was asking
him out, and I was like, "What?"

32:55.006 --> 32:56.166
<i>Is he cute?</i>

32:56.240 --> 32:57.605
Yes, but you're
missing the point.

32:59.410 --> 33:01.742
Hold on, Caroline.

33:01.813 --> 33:02.837
Angie?

33:02.914 --> 33:05.041
<i>I'm starving!</i>

33:05.116 --> 33:06.140
Well, look in
the refrigerator,

33:06.217 --> 33:09.414
there's a big container of
Monster Health Pea Soup.

33:09.487 --> 33:12.547
This looks really weird and
healthy. I don't like it.

33:12.623 --> 33:13.954
It's good for you.

33:14.025 --> 33:15.083
I'm not trying
to be dramatic,

33:15.159 --> 33:17.787
but I would rather be shot in the
face than eat this stupid food.

33:17.996 --> 33:20.760
Angie, just eat it, okay? Bye.

33:20.832 --> 33:25.292
Caroline? She's crazy. It
is like living with a child.

33:25.570 --> 33:27.367
Well, you know,
you will literally be

33:27.438 --> 33:28.928
living with a child soon.

33:29.007 --> 33:30.702
Maybe you need
to just get used to it.

33:30.775 --> 33:32.140
Alex! Alex!

33:32.276 --> 33:35.439
Wait. I'm an adult. She's an
adult. We will work this out.

33:37.815 --> 33:41.649
You know, studies show that babies can
learn a second language in the womb.

33:41.719 --> 33:44.381
You know, you should play an English
tape, so it can come out talking,

33:44.455 --> 33:46.821
and it can be in commercials,
and you'll make a lot of money.

33:46.891 --> 33:50.725
<i>Next.
The elephant has big ears.</i>

33:53.097 --> 33:56.624
Your CD's skipping.
I'm gonna watch TV instead.

34:00.571 --> 34:03.404
<i>Oh, man. This show's awesome. In this
next clip is a dad playing baseball</i>

34:03.474 --> 34:04.463
<i>with his son.</i>

34:05.109 --> 34:06.508
That kid's gonna
hit his dad in the nuts.

34:06.577 --> 34:07.874
<i>Beautiful day! What
could possibly go wrong?</i>

34:07.945 --> 34:10.139
Hey, have you seen
this one before?

34:10.214 --> 34:13.012
You have a kid with a Wiffleball
bat and a dad with a crotch.

34:13.083 --> 34:15.210
<i>Proudest moment in any
father-son relationship.</i>

34:15.286 --> 34:18.619
You know, it's not gonna be
funny if you ruin the ending!

34:18.688 --> 34:21.089
<i>Here comes the pitch!</i>

34:22.827 --> 34:26.024
It is!
It's still funny!

34:28.699 --> 34:29.996
Oh, man.

34:30.068 --> 34:33.299
Did you just stick your
gum under my coffee table?

34:33.371 --> 34:35.202
I don't know.
- What do you mean, you don't know?

34:35.273 --> 34:36.797
Do you think you're
at an Arby's right now?

34:36.873 --> 34:38.670
You know what? I wish
